About Us
Quality and freshness doesn’t come easy, which is why we have a fantastic group of people working around the clock at Woolworths Distribution Centres to tackle the mind boggling logistical challenge of coordinating supplies from the farm-gate to supermarket shelves across the state.
Our Distribution Centres are also a critical control point in checking the quality of fresh food and placing it in the optimal conditions to protect its flavour, freshness and texture. Alongside the top service we provide to our supermarkets we also have super performance in our Distribution Network which store stock for many of our other brands such as BWS, Dan Murphy’s, Big W, Masters Home Improvement to mention just a few.
An exciting opportunity currently exists for a talented Transport Analyst to join our National Transportation Team. Your role within the Woolworths transport team will be to provide extensive analytical support in developing and testing the viability of transport solutions and other strategic initiatives and improvements.
You will
Work on modelling and analysis to develop improvements to transport or DC Operation;
Carry out network analysis including analysing logistics information, developing datasets and analysing existing operations;
Investigate new areas of opportunity with the business to reduce cost, time and waste;
Develop new solutions that are unique to Woolworths or the industry;
Plan an active role in projects and provide timely analytical support:
Develop processes and tools and provide technical support
Build stakeholder relationships to understanding business drivers
You will have
Transport / Supply Chain / SQL Modelling experience;
Proven experience as an Analyst in a logistics network environment;
Strong analytical and conceptual capability;
High commercial/financial acumen;
Cost benefit analysis experience;
Effective time management, report writing and documentation skills;
Experience in collaborating with others and working in a team to achieve outcomes;
Advanced Skills in MS Office (especially Excel and Access) and Google Docs;
Clear and concise communication skills and the ability to influence and negotiate
What we offer
Attractive remuneration package - including base salary, superannuation and annual bonus
Added benefits - including staff discounts, potential flexibility to work from different sites, healthcare, social club and much more (Site dependant)
Tech options - Woolworths are the largest employer of Google Apps in Australia, are early adopters of Agile and have Bring Your Own Device options too
Work variety - the opportunity to work on multiple brands and sizeable projects
Training and education - we pride ourselves in helping you realise your potential and give you the opportunity to be innovative
An exciting career - as our business grows, so do the opportunities for our people
Want to connect? Connect with me on LinkedIn Sarah Turner. We’re also social! - connect with us at #WOWcareers through LinkedIn #LI , Facebook, Instagram or via www.wowcareers.com.au
As part of creating a safe working environment, our Distribution Centres operates under a Drug & Alcohol Policy for all those on site. Employees are subject to possible random testing, and applicants to this role can expect to undergo tests as part of the recruitment process, in addition to a full physical."
